Available Skill
🔍 soap-parity-check
What this skill does

soap-parity-check analyzes a single SOAP operation and determines whether an equivalent REST endpoint exists in the codebase.

It automatically:

parses WSDL definitions
compares SOAP fields against REST DTOs and controllers
produces a gap analysis
generates Jira-ready Markdown output

Example Workflow

A typical engineering workflow using this skill:

SOAP operation identified
        ↓
Run soap-parity-check
        ↓
Copilot generates gap analysis
        ↓
Jira ticket or comment created
        ↓
REST parity work tracked and implemented

All outputs are formatted in Markdown and paste directly into Jira without formatting changes.

How to Enable the Skill in a Repository

GitHub Copilot loads skills based on instructions defined in:

.github/copilot-instructions.md
Step 1 — Create the instructions file

Create this file in your repository if it does not already exist:

.github/copilot-instructions.md
Step 2 — Add the trigger phrase

Add the following line:

Run soap-parity-check for {SOAP_OPERATION_NAME} from {ServerEI|ServerUI}

This tells Copilot when to activate the skill.

How to Use the Skill

Open GitHub Copilot Chat inside your repository and run:

Run soap-parity-check for Customer.List from ServerUI

